<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Dragoon on Balance Guides</title><link>https://www.thebalanceffxiv.com/jobs/melee/dragoon/</link><description>Recent content in Dragoon on Balance Guides</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Sun, 30 Mar 2025 10:51:36 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://www.thebalanceffxiv.com/jobs/melee/dragoon/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Dragoon Leveling Guide</title><link>https://www.thebalanceffxiv.com/jobs/melee/dragoon/leveling-guide/</link><pubDate>Sun, 30 Mar 2025 10:51:36 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.thebalanceffxiv.com/jobs/melee/dragoon/leveling-guide/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="dragoon-leveling-guide">Dragoon Leveling Guide&lt;/h1>
&lt;h2 id="gear">Gear&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Always use the highest Item Level gear available to you. The increase of Strength and survivability outweighs potentially more favorable substats in lower Item Level gear. The total amount of substats is also higher.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Dragoons use Maiming armor and Slaying accessories.
Low level gear may not be labeled as such, so make sure you always equip gear that gives a bonus to Strength.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="know-your-role">Know Your Role&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Melee DPS jobs have a unique mechanic in Positionals. Certain actions will deal more damage when executed from the rear or flank of a target. Targets with continuous Target Rings will always take the increased damage from positional actions. &lt;br>
The Role Action True North allows you to disregard positional requirements for ten seconds per use. &lt;br>
A continuous target ring will always count positionals as successful, regardless of your position.

&lt;div class="md__image">
 &lt;img id="[492 165 433 183 481 496]" src="https://imgur.com/ANOqtwM.png" onclick="openModal(this.id)" alt="Positional zones" title="Positional zones" />
&lt;/div>
&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Dragoon Basic Guide</title><link>https://www.thebalanceffxiv.com/jobs/melee/dragoon/basic-guide/</link><pubDate>Sun, 30 Mar 2025 10:51:04 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.thebalanceffxiv.com/jobs/melee/dragoon/basic-guide/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="jobsmeleedragoonopenerjobsmeleedragoonopenersaving-the-dragoon">&lt;a href="https://www.thebalanceffxiv.com/jobs/melee/dragoon/opener/">/jobs/melee/dragoon/opener/&lt;/a>Saving The Dragoon&lt;/h1>
&lt;h2 id="overview">Overview&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Dragoon is a relatively static melee DPS job with a high focus on weaving off-Global Cooldown (oGCD) actions between a rigid 10-hit sequence of Global Cooldown (GCD) actions. Burst windows can get hectic, and prioritizing the various skills you need to execute can become a rather significant hassle in some instances. Dawntrail has doubled down on this by introducing the ability to utilize even more oGCD actions at regular intervals, as if we didn’t have enough already.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Dragoon Skills Overview</title><link>https://www.thebalanceffxiv.com/jobs/melee/dragoon/skills-overview/</link><pubDate>Sun, 30 Mar 2025 10:49:31 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.thebalanceffxiv.com/jobs/melee/dragoon/skills-overview/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="dragoon-skills-overview">Dragoon Skills Overview&lt;/h1>
